{#
  Deflect prompt — delivery-exception triage handled entirely from the KB
  and a status lookup. No mutating tool call.

  Context variables:
    user_question: string
    delivery: { id, status, eta, stop_sequence, exception_code }
    kb_excerpts: list[ {title, snippet, url} ]
#}
The dispatcher asked:

  "{{ user_question }}"

Delivery on file:
  id:               {{ delivery.id }}
  status:           {{ delivery.status }}
  eta:              {{ delivery.eta }}
  stop in route:    {{ delivery.stop_sequence }}
  exception code:   {{ delivery.exception_code | default("none") }}

Relevant KB excerpts:

{% for excerpt in kb_excerpts | default([]) -%}
[{{ loop.index }}] {{ excerpt.title }}
{{ excerpt.snippet }}
({{ excerpt.url | default("kb://internal") }})

{% endfor %}

Explain the exception code in plain dispatcher language, cite the KB
excerpt that defines it, and give one recommended action. Keep the reply
to <= 4 sentences. Do not call any mutating tool in this turn.
